## Authority Principles

- Maturity does not grant execution authority.
- Readiness does not grant production authority.
- Business can classify, coordinate, prepare handoffs and route escalation, but cannot execute sensitive actions.
- Governance approval is required for DAO, proposal, voting, federation, constitutional or governance-plugin actions.
- Treasury approval is required for funds, custody, settlement, revenue, debenture, billing, payout or treasury exposure.
- Architecture review is required for cross-nucleus contracts, persistence, APIs, UI consumption, provider selection and ownership transfers.
- Execution review is required for wallet signing, on-chain writes, trading, DEX swaps, marketplace settlement, mining payouts, lottery execution, ACS provisioning, production credentials or live provider action.

## Action Authority Levels

| Level | Name | Allowed Actions | Prohibited Actions | Required Approvals | Evidence Requirements |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| LEVEL_0_DOCUMENTATION | Documentation | Status, reports, roadmaps, handoffs, local registries | Production claims, publication without authority, execution approval | Business or Documentation review | Source docs and boundary statement |
| LEVEL_1_READINESS | Readiness | Assessments, maturity reviews, blocker mapping, handoff packages | Implementation, execution, fund movement, production operation | Business review plus owner review if sensitive | STATUS, maturity assessment, blocker register |
| LEVEL_2_READ_ONLY | Read-only | Read-only data, mock/provider visibility, dashboards without transaction controls | Mutations, signing, transaction submission, settlement, payouts | Architecture review where cross-nucleus | Read-only contract and boundary tests |
| LEVEL_3_LOCAL_VALIDATION | Local validation | Local tests, mock/local fixtures, local DB validation, static scanners | Production DB, production credentials, external execution | Owning nucleus plus Architecture if needed | Validation report and non-production config |
| LEVEL_4_CONTROLLED_INTEGRATION | Controlled integration | Read-only or guarded integration planning with explicit fallback and no execution | Required provider dependency, hidden write path, live fund impact | Architecture plus owning nucleus review | Contract, rollback, health/freshness and risk evidence |
| LEVEL_5_EXECUTION_SENSITIVE | Execution-sensitive | Planning only unless separately approved | Wallet signing, swaps, trading, settlement, payouts, treasury movement, ACS provisioning, on-chain writes | Owning nucleus, Governance/Treasury/Security/Portfolio Board as applicable | Separate execution request, audit/rollback/security evidence |
| LEVEL_6_PRODUCTION | Production | None currently authorized by this review | Production claims, production users/funds/credentials/services | Explicit production governance approval | Production approval record, audit and operations evidence |

## Boundary Classification Model

| Classification | Meaning |
|---|---|
| NON_EXECUTIVE | May coordinate, document, classify or prepare handoffs; cannot execute product or financial workflows. |
| READ_ONLY | May expose or consume read-only data; cannot mutate state or initiate execution. |
| MOCK_LOCAL | May run mock/local validation or fixtures; no external execution. |
| EXECUTION_SENSITIVE_BLOCKED | Owns a sensitive execution domain, but execution is currently blocked. |
| GOVERNANCE_GATED | Requires governance approval before advancement. |
| TREASURY_GATED | Requires treasury/financial approval before advancement. |
| PRODUCTION_GATED | Requires production authority before external operation. |
| EXECUTION_AUTHORIZED | Explicit execution authority exists. Not used in the current portfolio state. |
| UNKNOWN | Evidence is insufficient. |

## Boundary Classification Summary

| Nucleus | Boundary Classification | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| Core | GOVERNANCE_GATED | L5/pre-RC architecture authority, but consumer pilots and RC approval remain explicit gates. |
| Governance | GOVERNANCE_GATED | Governance authority owner, but proposal/vote/executor/mutation paths remain blocked. |
| Documentation | NON_EXECUTIVE | Publication governance exists, but publication authority and versioning remain blocked. |
| Dex | READ_ONLY | L4 readiness is read-only/provider reliability; DEX swaps and routing execution are blocked. |
| Defi | TREASURY_GATED | Treasury/custody planning exists; treasury execution remains blocked. |
| AxodusAPP | READ_ONLY | Integration shell and presentation layer; wallet/trading execution remains blocked. |
| Business | NON_EXECUTIVE | L4 consolidated coordination and classification nucleus; no execution authority. |
| Marketplace | EXECUTION_SENSITIVE_BLOCKED | Owns marketplace settlement/payment boundaries; execution blocked. |
| Academy | EXECUTION_SENSITIVE_BLOCKED | Rewards/certification/contract execution blocked. |
| Mining | TREASURY_GATED | Provider/payout/custody boundaries require treasury approval. |
| ACS | EXECUTION_SENSITIVE_BLOCKED | Runtime/provisioning/autonomy authority blocked. |
| Trading | EXECUTION_SENSITIVE_BLOCKED | Trading, credentials and exchange execution blocked. |
| BBA-Agency | MOCK_LOCAL | L3 service delivery evidence; real billing/campaign/client execution blocked. |
| Lottery | EXECUTION_SENSITIVE_BLOCKED | Randomness/prize/payout/compliance execution blocked. |

